{
  "stem": "10406.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Being that, in a way, the majority in-- in-- in school was Jewish because of the concentration of population there, we-- we did not feel different from that sense.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Being that this was under Polish control, all of the official posts, like the post office and the-- and the police, it was all controlled by Polish Catholics, including all the teachers were Polish Catholics.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was a little uneasiness from that point of view, because there was-- especially with from the nationalistic Polish population-- there was a sense of antisemitism.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And during that particular period, Hitler was already doing his thing in-- in Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And information was feeding back to Poland quite rapidly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was already an organized Polish antisemitism in some of the extreme parties, especially the right.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were some extreme right parties that were beginning to-- to organize boycotts on Jewish stores, although not in our town in particular.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was already the going things in other parts.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To a lesser extent, because the-- the non-Jewish boys would-- would-- especially the Polish boys-- would tend to look down at the, even though we were in a sense a majority in town, as second class citizens in a way.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For some reason, the Polish mind never saw a Jew as being a Polish citizen per se.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would always-- and any-- if they wanted to taunt us or in any way in insulting, they would always say Zydzi do Palestyny, Jews to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They knew we didn't belong there for some reason, that we should leave in other words and go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not very much, although with neighbors like-- there-- my grandfather lived on a street that was already more mixed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so we would go into their houses once in a while.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
